jobs.description:
A member of the senior leadership team, I defined and managed the firm’s HR strategy and operations, with a focus on scaling and formalising programs following a period of significant growth for the business. With ownership of the HR and recruitment budget, I drove improvements across processes and practices to realise significant cost savings, reinvesting resources into external consulting expertise to establish best practice HR frameworks. During this tenure, I provided leadership to 5 HR staff, overseeing all activities spanning conflict management, compensation & benefits, recruitment, development and succession planning.
•	Improved legal staff retention by 10%, introducing strategically planned recruitment processes and coaching programs;
•	Increased staff engagement rates by >40% over 2 years, protecting the culture of the company through define peer groups;
•	Orchestrated the firm’s first diversity program developing female leaders.

I worked with the lead employment partner at Hunt & Hunt to provide large clients, SMEs and individuals with legal advice and assistance specifically with respect to employment and work health and safety matters in the following areas:

- Dispute resolution – resolving conflicts in the workplace involving underpayment claims discrimination/harassment claims, workplace bullying, general protections claims, terminations and unfair dismissals;

- Contracts – drafting and reviewing contracts of employment, policies and procedures, and other workplace instruments;

- Compliance – assisting employers in matters involving potential breaches of workplace laws where the Fair Work Ombudsman is or may become involved; and

- Strategic and practical advice for employers to reduce the risk and incidence of workplace disputes.

My background includes working as part of Hunt & Hunt Lawyer's Corporate and Commercial group, and providing services including commercial advice and legal representation in a range of areas including estate litigation, commercial leasing, wills and family law.

Undertaking specialist family law legal services including:
Conducting client interviews;
Providing detailed advice on both property and parenting matters;
Negotiating settlements;
Drafting documents including letters of advice, offers of settlement and general correspondence.
Drafting court documents including Application for Divorce, Consent Orders, Initiating Applications and Affidavits;
Conducting legal research;
Writing articles;
Reporting on current legal issues and recent developments.

general.description:
I maintain a general practice at the private bar in Queensland, with an emphasis on commercial litigation, including  professional negligence, defamation, personal injuries, construction, estates, crime, family and native title law.


Specialties: 

Native Title - acted for Indigenous claimants and claimant groups, land councils, the State of Queensland, and mining companies in determination and ILUA matters, and indigenous corporation matters. Counsel for the State of Queensland in the Pitta Pitta, Djungan, Bularnu, Waluwarra and Wangkayujuru and Warrungnu determinations.

Personal Injury - Member WorkCover Queensland panel, provision of written advices and representation at court and mediation for plaintiffs and defendants.

Aviation - acted in commercial disputes, professional negligence and pilot licensing matters. 

Building and Construction - acted in all state courts in Subcontractors Charges Act, Building and Construction Industry Payments Act and related Corporations Act matters

Family - acted in Family Court and FCC in property and parenting matters, and as counsel for the Independent Childrens Lawyer.

Civil and Commercial - acted in all levels of both federal and state courts.

Crime - acted in all state courts in trials, applications and sentences.

• Argued appeals to the Queensland Court of Appeal and the Australian Capital Territory Supreme Court;
• Conducted trials in the Supreme, District and Magistrates Courts of Queensland;
• Prepared documents for and arguing in favour of and against many interlocutory applications concerning matters of practice and procedure, including applications for:
 security for costs;
 summary judgments/summary dismissals/strike outs;
 dismissal for want of prosecution;
 further and better disclosure and particulars;
 costs orders;
 joinder of parties;
 contempt applications;
 directions;
 various other procedures under the UCPR;


Liability limited by a scheme approved under Professional Standards Legislation.

