general.description:
I act for a wide range of predominantly global companies.  

I assist companies establish and maintain their operations in Australia and include among my clients some of the largest companies in the world.

I am one of the partners in charge of the corporate secretarial team at Baker McKenzie in Australia which maintains the corporate books and records and provides corporate secretarial services to almost a thousand companies in Australia– the majority of which are Australian subsidiaries of large multinational groups.

I have significant experience in reorganisations of corporate groups and am one of the leaders of Baker McKenzie’s Global Reorganisations Practice Group.

The Global Reorganisations Practice Group is a group which focuses on the design and implementation of complex domestic and cross border reorganisations of corporate groups, including:
•	packaging businesses prior to an IPO, spin-off or disposal;
•	post-acquisition integrations of acquired groups of companies;
•	supply chain restructuring or restructuring a group's arrangements for the 
development, ownership and exploitation of intellectual property;
•	reorganisations consequent upon the recapitalisation or refinancing of a group's operations;
•	reorganisations designed to reduce a group's worldwide effective tax rate; and
•	corporate clean-up and group simplification projects.

